00:13:11.760 --> 00:13:15.320
So is it possible to run Posit Connect on-premise?

00:13:15.400 --> 00:13:17.159
If so, is there a cost?

00:13:17.159 --> 00:13:21.400
So Posit Connect is a tool, again, that we've built here at Posit, one of our professional

00:13:21.400 --> 00:13:25.280
tools within that Posit team ecosystem.

00:13:25.280 --> 00:13:30.099
And Posit Connect is meant to be installed on a Linux server that you maintain.

00:13:30.099 --> 00:13:32.520
And where that Linux server is, is completely up to you.

00:13:32.520 --> 00:13:36.400
If you want to have a physical server right next to your computer and install Posit Connect

00:13:36.400 --> 00:13:37.400
on it, you can do that.

00:13:37.400 --> 00:13:41.520
If you want to have it hosted in the cloud in a virtual machine, you can absolutely do

00:13:41.520 --> 00:13:42.520
that as well.

00:13:42.719 --> 00:13:46.599
So that's one of the benefits of Posit Connect, is it gives your team the flexibility to install

00:13:46.599 --> 00:13:49.200
it on a Linux server, wherever that server may be.

00:13:49.200 --> 00:13:50.840
And it could be a single server.

00:13:50.840 --> 00:13:55.559
It could be a compute cluster using something like Kubernetes or Slurm.

00:13:55.559 --> 00:13:56.559
You can also integrate.

00:13:56.559 --> 00:14:00.919
Well, at least Kubernetes, you can integrate with Posit Connect.

00:14:00.919 --> 00:14:02.799
And yes, there is a cost with Posit Connect.

00:14:02.799 --> 00:14:07.299
So if you're curious to know a little bit about the cost, we'd encourage you to reach

00:14:07.299 --> 00:14:09.039
out to us here at Posit.

00:14:09.039 --> 00:14:12.400
I believe you can use sales at posit.co.

